# 🚀 Employee Management System (Core Java)

A console-based Employee Management System built using **Core Java**.

---

## 📌 Features

- 🔐 Simple Login Authentication (Maximum 3 Login Attempts)
- ✅ Add Employee
- ✅ View Employees
- ✅ Search Employee
- ✅ Update Salary
- ✅ Delete Employee
- ✅ Sort Employees by Salary
- 💾 Save Employee Data using Serialization
- 📂 Load Employee Data using Deserialization

This project is a console-based Employee Management System developed using Core Java to demonstrate Object-Oriented Programming, Collections Framework, Java Streams, File Handling, and Serialization concepts.

The application provides CRUD operations for employee records along with secure login authentication and persistent data storage using Serialization.

---

## 🛠 Technologies Used

- Java
- OOP
- Collections Framework
- Streams API
- Optional
- Serialization
- File Handling
- Exception Handling

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```
src/
 ├── main
 ├── model
 ├── service
 └── util
```

---

## ▶️ How to Run

1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <repo-url>
```

2. Compile

```bash
javac *.java
```

3. Run

```bash
java Main
```

